{
  "stem": "23942.6",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was even showing her, by-- you know, by example what, what it is-- how good it is to be a-- I mean, I was so already into it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, I think I was-- my-- my brain-- my head was already-- how do you say?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They convinced me that it wasn't worthy to be a Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I really felt it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that point, I met many children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they told me the same thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, one girl I met, she was hidden by the nuns in Przemysl.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when they came to pick her up, she says-- she saw a man with beard-- said, that dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's what it was like to some of the children after being exposed to-- not-- you know, against their own religion, that in other words, they thought that the Catholic religion was more important, and theirs was nothing.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After all, I didn't have any introduction to Jewish history till then.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't have-- I wasn't taught anything of my own culture, of my own history, of my own-- all I remember that my family, we celebrated Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What does that mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't know anything, how to protect and defend my own religion.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wasn't told.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So how could I speak up for myself?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I thought, since I was taught the non-Jew, I was taught to, to do what I was taught during the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I didn't think mine was important.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I really-- I really didn't think I, I wanted, even, to become-- stay Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't think-- I didn't see anything in it anymore because I wasn't-- it wasn't learned in the-- in other words, I wasn't taught anything-- or how to read, or write, or history, or, or anything of Jewish.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
